\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. G. papillosa }Porta, {\b Atti Accad. Agiati} ser. 3, {\b 11} ({\b 2}): 1 (1905) ({\i G. glandulosa} Porta, non Walpers, {\i G. fastigiata} auct. ital., non L.). Like {\b 7} but entirely glabrous; internodes shorter than leaves; leaves linear-lanceolate, long-acuminate; calyx-teeth apiculate; petals emarginate; capsule purplish; seeds with obtuse tubercles.{\i  Dry, stony ground. • N. Italy} ({\i near Garda}). It.
