\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. G. struthium }Loefl.,{\i  Iter Hisp.}{\b  79}: 303 (1758) ({\i G. iberica} Barkoudah). Plant more or less glabrous; rhizome woody, branched. Stems 20-100 cm, ascending to erect, branched. Leaves 10-50 × 1-2 mm. Inflorescence a loose panicle of dense clusters of flowers. Pedicels short, glabrous or glandular-pubescent. Calyx 1·5-3·5 mm. Petals c. 3 mm, cuneate, white. Seeds with long, acute, conical tubercles. {\i Gypsaceous soils. • C., E. & N. Spain.} Hs.
